WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:03.171
Previously on The Riches.

00:03.237 --> 00:05.106
[ Tires Screeching ]

00:07.975 --> 00:10.444
- Sorry.
- [ Dahlia ] You wanna pretend
to be the dead guy?

00:10.511 --> 00:12.613
You wanna wear his suits
and me to be his dead wife?

00:12.680 --> 00:14.682
[ Cael ]
Do you really think
Dad has a plan?

00:14.748 --> 00:20.088
He stole the money. Ma lost
the money. And now we're here
in a dead guy's house.

00:20.154 --> 00:22.156
How'd y'all get
in the front gate?
We live here.

00:22.223 --> 00:23.491
Come and meet
our new neighbors.

00:23.557 --> 00:25.859
- Hi, Nina. Can I come in?
- Well, sure, honey.

00:25.926 --> 00:30.164
Doug Rich
was a securities lawyer,
whatever that is.

00:30.231 --> 00:34.602
This is not my specialty.
I'm a securities lawyer.

00:34.668 --> 00:36.770
With your experience,
it should be a piece of cake.

00:36.837 --> 00:40.007
Doug is a Republican.
His best friend is Pete.

00:40.074 --> 00:42.976
Pete's a mortgage broker
from Dallas. He's e-mailed
twice about a golf trip.

00:43.043 --> 00:46.714
Why are we gettin' a bill
from Mountain View Nursing Home
for $4700 a month?

00:46.780 --> 00:48.882
[ Cael ]
Must be where
Cherien's mother is.

00:48.949 --> 00:51.252
Come on, Ma.
We're getting outta here.

00:51.319 --> 00:54.822
- It's Cherien's mom.
- She likes it here.

00:57.291 --> 00:59.827
Can you not read the sign?

00:59.893 --> 01:03.030
I've already availed my services
to some of your neighbors.
Your backdoor neighbor.

01:03.097 --> 01:06.033
Doug Rich?
That's his name?

01:06.100 --> 01:08.502
So Doug Rich,
he really screwed you over
on that paint job.

01:08.569 --> 01:11.805
He can suck shit in hell
for all I care.

01:11.872 --> 01:14.575
Hugh's not back yet.
What do you mean,
he's not back yet?

01:14.642 --> 01:16.110
Uh, where is he?
What's he doing?

01:16.177 --> 01:20.414
- Hugh, where are you?
- Somewhere in the desert,
I'm guessin'.

01:20.481 --> 01:24.418
As of this moment,
I am in control here.

01:29.223 --> 01:31.359
Aw, shit.

01:33.961 --> 01:36.130
[ Beeping ]

01:36.197 --> 01:38.199
[ Line Ringing ]

01:38.266 --> 01:40.368
[ Chattering ]

01:40.434 --> 01:42.570
Hey.

01:42.636 --> 01:46.507
Yeah, I just got
an e-mail from, uh, Pete.
You remember him.

01:46.574 --> 01:49.076
Yeah, he wants to come visit
his friend Doug.

01:49.143 --> 01:51.845
When did he e-mail?
Who e-mailed?

01:51.912 --> 01:53.481
Pete.
Pete who?

01:53.547 --> 01:55.383
Pete, Doug's best friend.
Best man at our wedding.

01:55.449 --> 01:56.884
Oh, that Pete.
Still wants
to come visit.

01:56.950 --> 02:00.188
Look, e-mail him back that both
Cherien and I have the flu.

02:00.254 --> 02:03.457
- No, make it bubonic plague.
- Bubonic plague?

02:03.524 --> 02:06.059
Yeah. Well,
he's unlikely to come over
if we got bubonic plague.

02:06.126 --> 02:08.296
That's dumb, honey.
Say it's hepatitis.

02:08.362 --> 02:10.864
Hepatitis.
And tell him it's more
contagious than mono.

02:10.931 --> 02:12.600
You're late.
No, I'm not.

02:12.666 --> 02:15.503
- It's 10:30.
- It's only a couple hours.

02:15.569 --> 02:18.639
- Well, he's back.
- Hugh?

02:18.706 --> 02:22.310
Oh, five days gone and
he waltzes in with no warning?

02:22.376 --> 02:25.012
Yup, and he does
not waltz in alone.

02:25.078 --> 02:27.948
Doug.
Great to see you.

02:28.015 --> 02:29.917
[ Pats Back ]

02:29.983 --> 02:34.255
Cherien.
Great to see you.

02:34.322 --> 02:36.524
Where the hell have you been?

02:36.590 --> 02:39.860
Aubrey, could you please
give us a minute?

02:39.927 --> 02:41.895
Thank you.

02:41.962 --> 02:44.865
Uh, I needed a break.

02:44.932 --> 02:47.167
I really did, after that
dinner party of yours.

02:47.235 --> 02:49.437
Got a little wild there.

02:49.503 --> 02:52.940
But I feel good now.
I feel real good.

02:53.006 --> 02:56.244
- Obviously.
- Hugh, five days.
We were worried.

02:56.310 --> 02:59.880
Oh, no. There's no need
for that. Old Hugh's not
falling down any rabbit hole.

02:59.947 --> 03:02.450
No, uh, I went to Taos,
did some spirit shit,

03:02.516 --> 03:06.754
some of that sweat lodge,
naked men bangin'
on drums thing.

03:06.820 --> 03:08.756
Cleaned myself right out.

03:08.822 --> 03:10.824
And there you met a--

03:10.891 --> 03:13.227
Gymnast.
That's GiGi.

03:13.294 --> 03:15.195
And she's a dancer.

03:15.263 --> 03:17.298
[ Chuckles ]

03:17.365 --> 03:22.236
After Taos, I felt so clean,
uh, and kinda gay.

03:22.303 --> 03:26.073
Kinda freaked me out.
Went right to Vegas.

03:26.139 --> 03:29.943
A miracle happened.
I fell in love.

03:30.010 --> 03:33.514
I really fell in love,
and in part because of...

03:33.581 --> 03:37.150
the inspirational nature
of your relationship,

03:37.217 --> 03:39.353
I married her--
I did.

03:39.420 --> 03:40.988
Lookit there.
Lookit.

03:41.054 --> 03:44.325
You don't fool around,
do you?
I trust my instincts, Doug.

03:44.392 --> 03:46.860
I always have. Oh.
Tiny thing.

03:46.927 --> 03:51.499
I neglected to have
her sign a prenup,
so fix that, will you?

03:51.565 --> 03:54.167
- Prenup?
- I learned the hard way.

03:54.234 --> 03:56.003
Everything needs to
be in writing. Okay?

03:56.069 --> 03:58.306
And have it wrapped up
by Saturday before the party.

03:58.372 --> 04:01.742
- What party?
- My wedding reception.

04:03.143 --> 04:04.878
Come here, sugarplum.

04:04.945 --> 04:07.615
Mmm, mmm, mmm.
Yeah.

04:21.061 --> 04:23.597
[ Arm Whirring ]

04:31.171 --> 04:33.273
[ Clears Throat ]

04:37.044 --> 04:39.347
Well, look at you
all clean.

04:39.413 --> 04:41.315
Is that how you like it,
Dale? Clean?

04:41.382 --> 04:43.917
No, ma'am, I certainly do not.

04:43.984 --> 04:46.787
You've been playing
with my arm, haven't you?

04:48.889 --> 04:50.758
No.

04:52.059 --> 04:53.994
Haven't you?

04:54.061 --> 04:56.129
I like it.

04:56.196 --> 04:59.367
Oh, you like it.

05:00.468 --> 05:02.370
Well, I like
that you like it.

05:02.436 --> 05:04.037
You do?
Mm-hmm.

05:05.339 --> 05:08.742
[ Coughing ]
Oh, sh--

05:08.809 --> 05:12.780
Well, hi, darlin'.
I was just checkin'
the rat traps.

05:12.846 --> 05:16.450
They look good.
Your Lucky Charms
are on the table.

05:16.517 --> 05:18.952
- I'll be in in a second.
- [ Everett Coughing ]

05:20.220 --> 05:23.357
Stop.

05:23.424 --> 05:26.293
Oh, you're bad.
Oh, you have no idea.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.529
Oh.

05:42.109 --> 05:44.812
[ Arm Whirring ]
[ Moans ]

05:50.150 --> 05:53.487
I just-- I don't understand.
I don't. What is a prenup?

05:53.554 --> 05:59.493
Well, it's a kind of contract
thing the buffers make
before they tie the knot,

05:59.560 --> 06:02.195
'cause basically
they don't trust each other.

06:02.262 --> 06:05.065
Then why would
they get married?

06:05.132 --> 06:07.401
It's a different way
of thinking, baby.
I don't understand.

06:07.468 --> 06:10.170
How can you have a prenup
if you already "nupped"?

06:10.237 --> 06:12.573
Then it's a postnup.

06:12.640 --> 06:14.908
And why would she sign that?

06:14.975 --> 06:18.812
I mean, she got him right
where she wants him. Damn.

06:18.879 --> 06:21.815
Okay, we got a problem
with your pal, Pete.

06:21.882 --> 06:23.951
Yeah? We're sick.
We got hepatitis.

06:24.017 --> 06:26.086
Yeah, he's sorry about that,
feels real bad.

06:26.153 --> 06:29.923
The thing is, he's gonna be in
town and he really wants to see
his old buddy, Doug.

06:29.990 --> 06:32.125
He's coming anyway.
He's comin' anyway.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.162
Oh, shit, Wayne.

06:59.653 --> 07:01.655
So what are we supposed
to do, Wayne,

07:01.722 --> 07:03.491
when he shows up here looking
for Doug and Cherien Rich?

07:03.557 --> 07:06.594
How did he even
get the address?
Doug must have given it to him.

07:06.660 --> 07:10.130
We could go light out.
We could stay in the R.V.
for a couple of days.

07:10.197 --> 07:12.833
Why don't we just leave?
I don't want to leave.

07:12.900 --> 07:14.902
I don't want to sleep
in the R.V. anymore, Dad.

07:14.968 --> 07:17.370
- What time's he coming?
- Sometime tomorrow.

07:17.437 --> 07:20.107
We just tell him the Riches
have moved. We have no idea
where they've gone.

07:20.173 --> 07:22.543
Real sorry. See you later.

07:22.610 --> 07:25.378
No, I say we tell him nothing
about the Riches.

07:25.445 --> 07:28.482
We aren't the Riches.
We don't know the Riches.
We never met the Riches.

07:28.549 --> 07:33.687
When he shows up,
we just tell him we're the--
the Montpierre family.

07:33.754 --> 07:36.423
Wayne and Dahlia Montpierre.

07:36.490 --> 07:38.526
- Dad, that's retarded.
- I'm with her.

07:38.592 --> 07:41.261
- Sounds a lot like a sleeper.
- No, it can work.

07:41.328 --> 07:45.132
Just e-mail him back.
Tell him the fever has broken.
Come around about 5:00.

07:45.198 --> 07:48.569
Okay? Right.
We are gonna de-Rich this house.

07:48.636 --> 07:51.939
I have to pee.
Oh, God in heaven.

07:59.913 --> 08:02.049
[ Beeps ]

08:02.115 --> 08:05.586
Hi-- Shit.
[ Beeps ]

08:12.860 --> 08:15.863
Hi, this is-- Shit.
[ Beeps ]

08:18.431 --> 08:21.001
[ Beeps ]

08:21.068 --> 08:23.003
Hi, leave a message.

08:29.109 --> 08:32.145
No, GiGi, it's not a prenup.
It's a postnup.

08:32.212 --> 08:34.414
As in after nuptials.

08:34.481 --> 08:36.516
I know what it is.

08:36.584 --> 08:38.719
Bullshit.

08:39.987 --> 08:42.322
I assure you, this is a very
normal legal document.

08:42.389 --> 08:46.493
A postnup is a typical thing
you sign if you haven't
signed a prenup.

08:46.560 --> 08:50.197
Well, if that's the way Hugh
feels, then we should just call
the whole thing off.

08:50.263 --> 08:52.099
I don't want anything of his.

08:52.165 --> 08:55.335
I'm-I'm a college graduate.
I can take care of myself.

08:55.402 --> 08:57.871
I'm sure you can.
I need a Coke.

08:58.872 --> 09:01.308
Ah. That didn't go
too well, huh?

09:01.374 --> 09:04.211
Doug!

09:04.277 --> 09:08.716
From what I just saw,
my bride doesn't look happy.

09:08.782 --> 09:10.784
She didn't buy the offer?

09:10.851 --> 09:13.053
I don't think
that's the problem.

09:13.120 --> 09:15.656
Not even the part about the
dance scholarship in her name?

09:20.327 --> 09:23.063
I really like your vest.

09:23.130 --> 09:25.666
Oh, thanks.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.936
You know, it's not
what you guys think.

09:29.002 --> 09:31.872
I'm not--
I'm not a gold digger.

09:31.939 --> 09:35.175
Put myself through college
by pole dancin'. So what?

09:35.242 --> 09:39.012
I don't need to justify myself
to you or anybody else.

09:39.079 --> 09:40.648
No, you don't.

09:40.714 --> 09:44.752
She feels that if you're
doubting the strength
of the union so early,

09:44.818 --> 09:46.887
perhaps it's best
you just walk away.

09:46.954 --> 09:50.023
What?
She has a point.

09:50.090 --> 09:53.026
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
What? I love her.

09:53.093 --> 09:55.362
I don't want to walk away.
I don't want to walk away.

09:55.428 --> 09:58.766
I just don't want her walkin'
away with half of Panco either,

09:58.832 --> 10:01.935
on the-- on the off, off, off,
remote chance...

10:02.002 --> 10:04.604
that somethin' does go sour.

10:04.672 --> 10:08.541
I've been honest with Hugh.
Told him I want more
for my life.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.610
What's wrong with that?

10:10.678 --> 10:13.246
Nothin', honey.
Everyone wants more.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.182
Even you?

10:15.248 --> 10:17.985
Workin' in a nice place
like this, classy as you are?

10:18.051 --> 10:19.953
Yeah, even me.

10:21.755 --> 10:24.291
With you marrying Hugh,

10:24.357 --> 10:28.428
I figure
I might move out of being
a personal assistant.

10:28.495 --> 10:30.764
Maybe be a sales associate.

10:30.831 --> 10:33.667
I think you'd be
real good at that.

10:33.734 --> 10:36.303
You carry yourself
with real authority, you know.

10:36.369 --> 10:38.238
I do?
Yeah.

10:38.305 --> 10:41.308
Thanks.
That's somethin'
I've been workin' on.

10:41.374 --> 10:46.780
Well, I'm workin' on--
I'm workin' on some things too.

10:46.847 --> 10:50.550
She's brought me love, Doug.
I'm a changed man.

10:50.617 --> 10:54.922
Really?
Took a long, hard look at
my life over the last five days.

10:54.988 --> 10:56.990
I realized
I was missin' somethin'.

10:58.491 --> 11:01.962
I was lonely.
Yeah.

11:02.029 --> 11:05.866
Now, you and Cherien,
you got somethin' there.

11:07.367 --> 11:12.172
It's-- Call it love,
call it chemistry.
Why shouldn't I have that?

11:12.239 --> 11:14.074
No reason.

11:14.141 --> 11:17.244
I figured you weren't
ever gonna hand over Cherien.

11:17.310 --> 11:19.947
What?
Then I met GiGi,

11:20.013 --> 11:24.918
and... it's just made me
a different person.

11:24.985 --> 11:28.421
I'm a kinder, gentler person.

11:32.059 --> 11:34.762
So, fix that, will you?

11:36.596 --> 11:38.498
I gotta call the caterer.

11:38.565 --> 11:41.601
She wants a white wedding,
and I'm gonna give it to her,
by God.

11:41.668 --> 11:44.872
[ Shouting ]
Kimmie, where's the
goddamn latte I asked for?

11:44.938 --> 11:47.307
I need my caffeine!

11:49.409 --> 11:51.578
Please.

11:51.644 --> 11:54.948
Do you think Hugh
really loves me,

11:55.015 --> 11:57.951
or am I just
a little Vegas toy?

11:58.018 --> 12:03.256
I think he loves you.
But, I mean, it's up to you
to decide what you are.

12:03.323 --> 12:06.259
Yeah.

12:06.326 --> 12:09.797
Would you tell me
if he didn't... love me?

12:11.698 --> 12:15.635
Yeah, if I was you,
I wouldn't.
It'd be easier to lie.

12:15.702 --> 12:18.939
[ Chuckles ]
It's always easier to lie.

12:19.006 --> 12:21.975
Excuse me.
Cherien, Dr. Cael
just phoned.

12:22.042 --> 12:26.179
It's almost 5:00.
Aw, shit.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.181
Bye.

12:28.248 --> 12:30.217
Bye.

12:40.794 --> 12:44.364
His car's out front.
He just pulled up, but he's
not gettin' out of the car.

12:44.431 --> 12:46.867
- Well, what's he doin'?
- [ Cael ]
Who knows?

12:46.934 --> 12:49.102
Okay, everybody ready?

12:51.171 --> 12:53.240
[ Car Door Closes ]
Shit.

12:59.346 --> 13:01.982
[ Doorbell Rings ]

13:03.350 --> 13:05.252
Shit!

13:07.620 --> 13:09.990
Hello.
Uh--

13:10.057 --> 13:12.860
Hi. Is-- Is, uh, Doug here?

13:12.926 --> 13:15.863
Doug. Doug who?

13:17.730 --> 13:20.000
Doug Rich.

13:21.034 --> 13:24.037
No. Uh, no Doug Rich.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.680
Montpierre?
Yes, I'm Wayne.

13:33.746 --> 13:36.483
And my wife, Dahlia--
Here she is.

13:36.549 --> 13:40.020
Darling, this is Pete--
Mincey. Pete Mincey.

13:40.087 --> 13:43.290
Hi. How do you do?
I'm Dahlia Montpierre.

13:43.356 --> 13:46.193
He's looking for his friend,
whose name is-- I am sorry.

13:46.259 --> 13:49.262
Doug Rich.
He e-mailed me he was sick.

13:49.329 --> 13:51.865
That's why I brought him
the soup.

13:51.932 --> 13:55.035
Oh, that's nice of you.
Uh, may I, uh--

13:55.102 --> 13:59.306
Yeah.
His friend used our house
as his home address.

13:59.372 --> 14:02.409
- And you've lived here--
- Little while now.

14:02.475 --> 14:07.147
- That's strange.
- Now, honey, is this someone
I should be concerned about?

14:07.214 --> 14:09.349
This Doug Rich person who
seems to know where we live.

14:09.416 --> 14:11.985
And, pardon me, but is
he involved in any kind
of criminal element?

14:12.052 --> 14:15.188
Because we do have children
to consider.

14:15.255 --> 14:18.892
No, certainly not.
Are you sure? Because,
uh, Dahlia is right.

14:18.959 --> 14:21.394
We have children.

14:21.461 --> 14:23.196
Come on. Go, go.

14:24.164 --> 14:26.699
- Hi, Mom. Hi, Dad.
- Hey.

14:26.766 --> 14:28.735
We're goin' to the park,
shoot some hoops with
the neighborhood kids.

14:28.801 --> 14:31.538
- Okay, well,
be back before dark.
- [ Sam ] Sure.

14:31.604 --> 14:33.907
Take care.
Hey, Mom.

14:33.974 --> 14:37.644
I just put the lasagna in the
oven. Want to know if there's
anything else I could do.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.513
No, sweetheart. Go on upstairs
and finish your homework.
Okay.

14:40.580 --> 14:43.183
Hi.

14:43.250 --> 14:45.452
They're good kids.
I'm so sorry
we couldn't help you.

14:45.518 --> 14:47.420
Yoohoo!
[ Knocking ]

14:47.487 --> 14:50.423
The front was open, so--
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't know
you had company.

14:50.490 --> 14:54.995
I was just going.
The Montpierres have been
more than kind.

14:55.062 --> 14:56.997
Uh-huh. Montpierres?
Yeah. That is--

14:57.064 --> 14:59.933
Oh, thank you
for your generosity,

15:00.000 --> 15:02.135
and thank you
so much for my tray.

15:02.202 --> 15:05.105
For bringin' that back.
And your understanding, Nina.

15:05.172 --> 15:08.141
Well, you're entirely welcome,

15:08.208 --> 15:11.378
Dahlia... Montpierre.

15:12.612 --> 15:15.482
So, Pete, I am sorry.
This is a dead end.

15:15.548 --> 15:17.417
Yeah, so sorry, Pete.

15:17.484 --> 15:19.452
I never thought Doug would
pull something like this.

15:19.519 --> 15:21.721
I mean, my best friend
and he's avoiding me?

15:21.788 --> 15:23.690
Well, it does happen.

15:23.756 --> 15:27.627
I guess I'm just gonna
have to try and track down
his ex-wife, Jolinda.

15:27.694 --> 15:30.163
Pete!

15:30.230 --> 15:32.865
It's almost 6:00.
Cocktail hour.

15:32.932 --> 15:36.369
We can't let you head out on
the open road without having
a cocktail, for God sakes.

15:36.436 --> 15:38.738
Yes, come and have
a cocktail.
Are you sure?

15:38.805 --> 15:41.308
Southern hospitality.

15:43.743 --> 15:46.346
So it's Jolinda Rich
from Tampa?

15:46.413 --> 15:50.683
I-I think so.
I only met her once.

15:53.987 --> 15:56.456
Got it.

15:56.523 --> 15:59.126
Told you he was good.

15:59.192 --> 16:02.695
Reception here is really awful.
If you'd like to try our phone,
there's one in the kitchen.

16:02.762 --> 16:07.267
- There might be more privacy.
- Okay. Thank you.
That was fast.

16:07.334 --> 16:10.570
It's on the counter.
Oh, I think I hear Grandma.

16:15.575 --> 16:18.511
[ Beeping ]

16:22.949 --> 16:24.884
[ Phone Buzzing ]

16:24.951 --> 16:26.986
Hello?

16:27.054 --> 16:29.756
Uh, is this Jolinda?
Jolinda Rich?

16:29.822 --> 16:31.758
Uh-huh.
Who's this speaking?

16:31.824 --> 16:37.130
Uh, this is Pete Mincey
from Tampa. I'm a friend
of your ex-husband's.

16:37.197 --> 16:39.732
Oh, yeah.
I remember you, Pete.

16:39.799 --> 16:42.702
Uh, good. Yeah.

16:42.769 --> 16:47.374
Okay. Um, listen,
I'm-I'm looking for Doug.

16:47.440 --> 16:51.678
Oh, well, join the club.
I ain't seen him
since he ran out on us.

16:51.744 --> 16:54.147
Well, uh--
